data.description:
Newly remodeled 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom frame home sitting on 30.42 acres in the little country community of Aleman.
The frame home was gutted to the studs with new floor plan designed which includes new subflooring, insulation, electrical, plumbing, septic tank, lateral lines, central heat & air unit, and throughout the home is laminate wood flooring. The kitchen & island Counter tops are quartz and a pot filler faucet built into the island. The bathroom counter tops are granite with mahogany cabinets. The home is all electric and the carport cover is wired for an RV or can be used to charge a car and incudes water & sewer connections. The acreage is fenced to run livestock and keep away from the house. Small barn with pens and water trough in pasture. Located off paved FM 932 with the house sitting in the middle. Bring your animals.
